title: Women in the United States House of Representatives
deleted: These are women who were elected on November 3, 2020 to serve in the United States House of Representatives but whose term of office has not commenced yet.  They are ordered, firstly, by the date on which their term of office is expected to commence and, secondly, alphabetically by surname.

title: Women in the United States House of Representatives
added: [[Chase G. Woodhouse]], born in [[British Columbia]], Canada, entered the House in 1945 to become the first foreign-born woman elected to either chamber. As of 2021, she has been the only Canadian female immigrant elected to Congress.
